Classes
Class
Description
Client
The `Client` class represents a client application that can connect to a server.
ClientHandler
The `ClientHandler` class is responsible for handling communication with individual clients connected to the server.
ClientMain
The `ClientMain` class serves as the entry point for running a client for the TestGameServer project.
ClientThread
The `ClientThread` class represents a client thread that connects to a server and sends a message.
ConfigHandler
The `ConfigHandler` class is responsible for managing configuration properties loaded from a file.
ConsoleListener
The `ConsoleListener` class provides functionality to redirect console output to log files and manage log files.
HelpPrint
The `HelpPrint` class provides methods for printing the content of a text file to the console.
MessageHandler
The `MessageHandler` class is responsible for handling and representing messages in the server.
MessageProcessor
The `MessageProcessor` class is responsible for processing incoming messages and executing various server tasks based on message content.
MessageReceiver
The MessageReceiver class is responsible for receiving and processing messages from the server.
Question
The `Question` class represents a question entity with its associated properties.
QuestionDatabaseHandler
The `QuestionDatabaseHandler` class manages a collection of questions and provides methods for adding, retrieving, and managing questions in a database.
Server
The `Server` class represents a basic server application for handling client connections and processing messages.
ServerMain
The `ServerMain` class is the entry point for the server application.
TeeOutputStream
The `TeeOutputStream` class extends `OutputStream` to duplicate output to two different output streams.
User
The `User` class represents a user entity with an ID, username, and password.
UserDatabaseHandler
The `UserDatabaseHandler` class manages a database of users stored in a text file.
